Daniel H. Schulman: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 22, 2017 2:24 AM ET
IT Services

Company Overview of PayPal Holdings, Inc.



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Daniel H. Schulman  Chief Executive Officer, President and Director, PayPal Holdings, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 6 Board Members in 6 different organizations across 14 different industries.See Board Relationships59$18,934,341As of Fiscal Year 2016
Background

		Mr. Daniel H. Schulman, also known as Dan, has been the President of PayPal Holdings, Inc. since September 30, 2014 and has been its Chief Executive Officer since July 2015. Mr. Schulman joined PayPal in 2014 to lead the PayPal into its next phase as an independent business. He served as the Group President of Enterprise Growth at American Express Company from August 2010 to September 30, 2014. At American Express, he was responsible for the its global strategy to expand ... alternative mobile and online payment services, form new partnerships and build revenue streams beyond the traditional card and travel businesses. He was also responsible for the American Express's Business Development, Mergers and Acquisitions unit. He has a record of high performance in the consumer-marketing arena and almost two decades of experience in the wireless industry. Mr. Schulman served as an Advisor at Greycroft Partners LLC. He served as the President of Prepaid Group at Sprint Corporation (Sprint Nextel Corporation) from 2009 to August 23, 2010. He served as President of Sprint Prepaid Group at Boost Mobile LLC. Mr. Schulman served as Founding Chief Executive Officer of Virgin Mobile USA, L.P. He served as Chief Executive Officer of Virgin Mobile USA, Inc. since October 2001 and served as its President. From May 2000 to May 2001, he served as the President and Chief Executive Officer of The Priceline Group Inc. (alternate name, Priceline.com Incorporated) since May 2000 and also served as its Chief Operating Officer since July 1999. He spent the early part of his career with AT&T, where he ultimately led its consumer long distance business. From December 1998 to July 1999, he served as the President of Consumer Markets Division of AT&T Corp. He served as a Member of AT&T Operations Group and served as its President of the Long Distance Division. From March 1997 to November 1998, Mr. Schulman served as the President of AT&T WorldNet Service. From December 1995 to February 1997, he served as the Vice President of Business Services Marketing of AT&T Business Markets Division and from May 1994 to November 1995, he served as a Small Business Marketing Vice President of AT&T Business Markets Division. He served for more than 18 years at&T. He has been the Non-Executive Chairman and Independent Director of Symantec Corporation since January 23, 2013 and March 2000 respectively. He has been Director at PayPal Holdings, Inc. since 2015 and serves as Director at Xoom Corporation. Mr. Schulman has been an Independent Director of Flex Ltd. since June 18, 2009. He served as a Director of The Telx Group, Inc. since February 2010 and Virgin Mobile USA, Inc. He served as Lead Director at Symantec Corporation from 2012 to January 23, 2013. Mr. Schulman served as a Director of Net2Phone, Inc., from September 1999 to September 2004. He served as a Director of iVillage Inc. He served as a Director of Veritas Software Corp. He serves on the Board of Autism Speaks and Rutgers University. Mr. Schulman serves as a Director of New Jersey Technology Council. He serves on the boards of several charitable organizations, including Teach for America. He received the New Jersey Ernst & He serves as a Trustee and Member of Board of Governors at Rutgers, The State University of New Jersey. He received Young Entrepreneur of the Year Award, saluting executives' efforts in business excellence and community improvement. He is named to Business Week's Top 20 People To Watch in media and FierceWireless' Top 25 Most Powerful People in the global wireless industry. Mr. Schulman holds an M.B.A., majoring in Finance and International Business from New York University and a B.A. Degree in Economics from Middlebury College.Read Full Background




